Possibilities of future governing arrangements were discussed, but nothing final was decided upon. The SF leadership act stoic, but can't quite hide their excitement at our overtures. 

[? if centenary = 0 : [+ sf_leader +] congratulates us on our upcoming centenary. ?]

Over the coming weeks, their members of paliament seem more talkative in the canteen.

@sf_rectification_of_history

The experience of the first [? if sf_failure = 1 : and second?] workers majorities have left a bitter taste in the mouth of many in our party. Perhaps by working out the causes of past failings together, we can help overcome mutual mistrust and reluctance. 

SF leaders now propose that parliamentarians from both parties should coauthor an official joint evaluation, identifying strategic mistakes made by both parties. 

Such a move could pave the way for further cooperation in the future.

- @sf_yes_history: A nice idea, lets do it.
- @sf_no_history: This is not in our interest.

